      • statsAsString

        public java.lang.String statsAsString()
        Description copied from interface: SparkTrainingStats
        Get a String representation of the stats. This functionality is implemented as a separate method (as opposed to toString()) as the resulting String can be very large.
        NOTE: The String representation typically includes only duration information. To get full statistics (including machine IDs, etc) use SparkTrainingStats.getValue(String) or export full data via SparkTrainingStats.exportStatFiles(String, SparkContext)
        Specified by:
